description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Care Network (PCN) Clinical Pharmacist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;£40-43,000 subject to experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;NHS pension, includes life insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;33 days annual leave plus bank holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Various locations across Sunderland&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;Full time - 37.5 hours, Part Time considered at a minimum of 0.5 whole time equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for pharmacists from all pharmacy sectors to join the Sunderland Primary Care Networks clinical pharmacy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an established and rapidly growing clinical pharmacy team comprising; a lead pharmacist, senior clinical pharmacists, clinical pharmacists and pharmacy technicians, providing innovative, high quality, patient centred care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for pharmacists to further expand our team who are enthusiastic, dedicated, have the ability to work autonomously as well as part of a team, be flexible due to the ever changing nature of primary care and can demonstrate leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be working as a member of one of our six PCNs and also part of the larger Sunderland wide team providing you with a well-supported network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful, you will be employed by Sunderland GP Alliance, on behalf of the PCNs. SGPA is a not-for-profit organisation owned by the city’s GPs, representing over 250,000 patients across Sunderland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role the successful candidates would be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake Structured Medication Reviews (SMRs) to proactively manage patients with complex polypharmacy and care home residents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be involved in the management of long term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the practices medication related workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to Multi-Disciplinary Teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilising independent prescribing expertise or support to achieve a qualification if not already held.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be expected to undertake training provided through the CPPE primary care pharmacy education pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more before applying, we are hosting an online engagement event where you can meet the Clinical Pharmacy team, PCN and SGPA representatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the perfect opportunity to find out more about the role and organisation and ask any questions you may have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘Working as a Sunderland PCN pharmacist’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wednesday 4th November 7-8pm &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;link to the event can be found in the Person Specification document.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also welcome any enquiries about this post so please feel free to contact us via email/telephone: Juliet Fletcher 0191 5128487&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing dates for the application are: 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews to be held: week commencing 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
